(AI Job Application Tracker) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Mentor walkthrough of the project for a senior Computer Science student with an AI) Tj
T*
(concentration.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Project Overview) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This project is a full-stack job application tracker with two input paths: manual entry) Tj
T*
(and automatic extraction from Outlook email. The goal is to keep a single source of) Tj
T*
(truth for applications and reduce the manual work of updating statuses as recruiters and) Tj
T*
(ATS systems send messages.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(At a high level, the architecture is:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ React/Next.js frontend for the dashboard UI) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ FastAPI backend for REST endpoints and email ingestion) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ SQLite database for persistence) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ Microsoft Graph API for reading Outlook mail) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ OpenAI plus regex parsing for extracting job details from emails) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The runtime flow is:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ The frontend loads the dashboard from frontend/src/app/page.tsx.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ It calls the backend through frontend/src/lib/api.ts.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ The backend starts in backend/app/main.py, mounts CRUD routes from) Tj
T*
(    backend/app/routes.py, and creates tables from models in backend/app/models.py.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ Application records are stored in SQLite using SQLAlchemy configured in) Tj
T*
(    backend/app/database.py.) Tj
ET
endstream
